Vice President Mike Pence spoke at the Manitowoc Cranes facility in Pennsylvania, praising American manufacturing and the progress made under President Trump. He highlighted the administration's efforts to cut red tape, reduce taxes, and promote American energy. Pence also emphasized the importance of passing the U.S.-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) and urged the audience to contact their elected representatives to support the trade deal. He noted that the USMCA would benefit Pennsylvania and create more jobs and opportunities for American workers. Pence concluded his remarks by expressing confidence in the future prosperity and security of Pennsylvania and the United States.